ENTRY       EC 6.3.2.31                 Enzyme
NAME        coenzyme F420-0:L-glutamate ligase;
            CofE-AF;
            MJ0768;
            CofE
CLASS       Ligases;
            Forming carbon-nitrogen bonds;
            Acid-D-amino-acid ligases (peptide synthases)
SYSNAME     L-glutamate:coenzyme F420-0 ligase (GDP-forming)
REACTION    GTP + coenzyme F420-0 + L-glutamate = GDP + phosphate + coenzyme F420-1 [RN:R09399]
ALL_REAC    R09399
SUBSTRATE   GTP [CPD:C00044];
            coenzyme F420-0 [CPD:C19153];
            L-glutamate [CPD:C00025]
PRODUCT     GDP [CPD:C00035];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            coenzyme F420-1 [CPD:C19152]
COMMENT     This protein catalyses the successive addition of two glutamate residues to cofactor F420 by two distinct and independent reactions. In the reaction described here the enzyme attaches a glutamate via its alpha-amine group to F420-0. In the second reaction (EC 6.3.2.34, coenzyme F420-1---gamma-L-glutamate ligase) it catalyses the addition of a second L-glutamate residue to the gamma-carboxyl of the first glutamate.
